{"article_id":"yhpj6ReKfSsuTgnj","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Al-Qaida in Yemen has taken responsibility for the attack on a satirical magazine in Paris","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that left 12 people dead .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"In a YouTube video , Nasr al-Ansi , a top commander of Al-Qaida in the Arabian Peninsula , said","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"the attack was in vengeance for the Prophet Muhammad .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"In a graphic","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"released on Twitter by the group ,","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"they say","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"the leadership of AQAP planned and financed the operation against Charlie Hebdo ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"which printed cartoon depictions of the prophet ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"despite threats .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"`` We did it in compliance with the Command of Allah","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"and supporting His Messenger , ''","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"the message read .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"In the almost 12-minute video , al-Ansi congratulates , Saïd and Chérif Kouachi , the two gunmen in Paris ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"and exhorts Muslims across the world to `` take vengeance for Muslim blood","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"spilled . ''","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"As al-Ansi speaks ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"video of the attack in Paris and of the Sept. 11 attacks on the World Trade Center plays in the background .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"`` Stop your insults on our prophet and sanctities , ''","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"al-Ansi says .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"`` Stop spilling our blood .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Leave our lands .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Quit plundering our resources . ''","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Otherwise ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"he says ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"`` you will look for peace and stability ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"but you will not find it . ''","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"The New York Times reports","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"that al-Ansi does not take responsibility for the attack on a Kosher supermarket","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"that started during the manhunt for the Kouachi brothers ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"but he does call Amedy Coulibaly ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"who","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"police say","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"perpetrated the attack ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"a `` mujahid brother . '' `` A member of Al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"who spoke to The New York Times on the condition of anonymity ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"the joint timing of the two operations was a result of the friendship between Mr. Coulibaly and the Kouachi brothers","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"and not a reflection of common planning between the Qaeda group and the Islamic State .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"`` Mr. Coulibaly ,","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"who had been imprisoned for a host of petty crime offenses ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"met Chérif Kouachi in jail ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"where Mr. Kouachi was serving time in 2005 and 2006","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"for belonging to a terrorist cell in Paris","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"that sent young men","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"to fight in Iraq . ''","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"There are two major U.S. plots","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"attributed to AQAP :","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"First in Dec. 25 , 2009 , Umar Farouk Abdulmutallab ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"colloquially known as the `` underwear bomber , ''","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"tried to detonate an explosive aboard a Detroit-bound flight .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"In 2010 , the organization was suspected of trying to pack explosives in printer ink cartridges .","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"J.M . Berger , a fellow at the Brookings Institution 's Project on U.S. Relations with the Islamic World , says","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"he does n't have any doubts","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"that Al-Qaida in the Arabian Peninsula played a role in the Paris attack .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"`` The question is exactly what that role is , ''","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"Berger said .","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"Berger says","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"that in other cases , AQAP has usually taken credit for an attack","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"and then released some kind of evidence","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"to corroborate their claim .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"He says","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"that may happen in this case , too .","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"Still ,","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"Berger says ,","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"this would be an unusual attack for AQAP ,","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"because","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"from what we know ,","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"it would have been perpetrated","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"years after the Koachi brothers are thought to have gone to Yemen .","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"Sajjan Goel , the international security director for the Asia-Pacific Foundation","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"who also teaches at London School of Economics ,","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"says","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"today 's announcement leaves a lot of open questions .","depth":3},{"id":74,"text":"Mainly :","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"Has AQAP established a line of communication between Yemen and operatives in the West ?","depth":5},{"id":76,"text":"And does this mean a shift in the mode of operation of AQAP .","depth":4},{"id":77,"text":"Goel says","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"in the past , AQAP has focused on sophisticated , bomb-based attacks on the airline industry .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"`` This plot would be a departure from their previous attacks , ''","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"he said .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":161,"left":150,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"par